2 tbsp olive oil|1
1 tbsp butter|1
1 onion , finely chopped|1
250g button chestnut mushroom , sliced|1
1 garlic clove , finely grated|1
100ml dry white wine|1
200ml double cream|1
1 lemon , zest only|1
200g parmesan (or vegetarian alternative), grated, plus extra to serve|1
300g tagliatelle or linguini|1
small bunch parsley , finely chopped|1
STEP 1Heat the oil and butter in a medium saucepan. Fry the onion over a low heat for 10 mins or until softened and translucent.|0
Heat the oil and butter in a medium saucepan. Fry the onion over a low heat for 10 mins or until softened and translucent.|0
Heat the oil and butter in a medium saucepan. Fry the onion over a low heat for 10 mins or until softened and translucent.|0
STEP 2Add the mushrooms and cook for 10 mins over a medium heat. Add the garlic and cook for 2 mins. Add the wine and bring to a simmer, reduce the liquid by half.|0
Add the mushrooms and cook for 10 mins over a medium heat. Add the garlic and cook for 2 mins. Add the wine and bring to a simmer, reduce the liquid by half.|0
Add the mushrooms and cook for 10 mins over a medium heat. Add the garlic and cook for 2 mins. Add the wine and bring to a simmer, reduce the liquid by half.|0
STEP 3Add the double cream and bring to a simmer, then add the lemon zest and parmesan. Season with salt and plenty of black pepper.|0
Add the double cream and bring to a simmer, then add the lemon zest and parmesan. Season with salt and plenty of black pepper.|0
Add the double cream and bring to a simmer, then add the lemon zest and parmesan. Season with salt and plenty of black pepper.|0
